ArcBall: arc ball implementation for visualisation control
BasicCamera: base camera class, defines default view to look down positive z axis (as oppose to negative z axis in OpenGL), allows accessor returns the intuitive camera position and orientation, the class internally handle the difference between view and model space
DraggableInterface: class for picking and dragging objects in OpenGL, using ray intersection
Keybinding: allows unique binding between keys and names of an action to be defined and queried
MiscUtils: misc functions, include getting seed from system and system time in seconds
Movement: subclass of Keybinding, caches results, designed for camera and object movement
QuakeCamera: implement Quake style camera using longitude and latitude parameterisation
QuatCamera: implementation Quaternion camera, allows full 3D rotation and translations
